fleets of research ships

01:09:42.380 --> 01:09:45.510
that can undertake that
90% of the world ocean.

01:09:45.510 --> 01:09:48.640
And even if you could
build that many ships,

01:09:48.640 --> 01:09:50.810
there's not enough
universities in the world

01:09:50.810 --> 01:09:55.190
that you could populate them
with trained scientists.

01:09:55.190 --> 01:09:56.500
So how do we get around that?

01:09:56.500 --> 01:10:00.400
And I think any AUVs,
autonomous unmanned vehicles,

01:10:00.400 --> 01:10:03.010
machines that can
do dumb science.

01:10:03.010 --> 01:10:06.130
That is, where you don't
require a human presence.

01:10:06.130 --> 01:10:08.360
You save the ships
for the kind of work

01:10:08.360 --> 01:10:11.430
requires human presence
at the work site.

01:10:11.430 --> 01:10:14.720
So I think that AUVs
that can be programmed

01:10:14.720 --> 01:10:19.140
to do surveys, data taking
over long periods of time

01:10:19.140 --> 01:10:19.970
autonomously.

01:10:19.970 --> 01:10:22.810
We're talking months,
maybe, on a mission.

01:10:22.810 --> 01:10:25.480
Coming up, transmitting,
data, satellite, back down.

01:10:25.480 --> 01:10:27.190
You could probably do that.

